reviews.review_text: best aud of this show My favorite of the available audience recordings given its clarity and expansiveness.  The show is the weakest of the tour arguably; sometimes the 3rd night in a city at that time would find them keeping it close to the ground with more of a likelihood of getting an (unwelcome in this case, I would imagine)  replacement of Fire with Estimated and then the less engaging Ship of Fools and Man Smart.  First set has great Touch of Grey and a good Birdsong typical of the era.  I wasn't happy with those new lyrics to BTW when I caught it a week later in Albany, but what can you do? First night of this run is the wackiest, second is probably the most powerful but I think the tour only improves after this.
Best Aud source I agree that this is best sounding version.  Not weakest show of tour.  Better than overrated 3/25 Albany.
